cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper deals with the problem of semantic labeling in remote sensing images using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new CNN architecture to encode rotation equivariance, which falls under the category of machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with the problem of land cover mapping, which falls under the category of graphics and visualization, making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible category. Finally, the paper uses rotating convolutions as building blocks, which falls under the category of robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category as well.
